parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Driver's Side Airbag to Deploy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver is not provided with the necessary protection to mitigate the impact of the collision.
symptoms: No airbag deployment in the event of a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the vehicle can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when stalling occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: and may restart after a brief period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shoulder/lap belts can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The male portion of the buckle won't stay locked into the female portion
the rear seat belts are inoperative
the rear seat belts cannot be securely fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the buckle assembly can cause the seat belts to malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the seat belt cannot be securely fastened

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained stalling of the engine can cause a loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to restart

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: the vehicle is difficult to start
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles when accelerating
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump relay clicks repeatedly.
